com.pb.sawdust.util.collections

Class AbstractSetDeque<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<E>
        • com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.AbstractSetQueue<E>
          • com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.AbstractSetDeque<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the elements held by this collection.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SetDeque<E>, SetQueue<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Deque<E>, java.util.Queue<E>, java.util.Set<E>

    public abstract class AbstractSetDeque<E>
extends AbstractSetQueue<E>
implements SetDeque<E>
    The AbstractSetDeque class provides a basic implementation of the SetDeque interface to lower the burden for programmers. Internally, it maintains a HashSet to ensure the set properties, and an implementation-specific Deque to ensure the deque properties.

                int loadFactor)

      • AbstractSetDeque

        public AbstractSetDeque(java.util.Collection<? extends E> c)
        Constructor which will create a new setdeque containing all of the elements in a specified collection. The setdeque will be initialized to the size of the collection. The ordering of the elements in the setdeque will be the same as the iteration order of the elements in the collection, whether or not the iteration order is well-defined.
        Parameters:
        c - The collection holding the elements which the setdeque will be initialized with.

    • Method Detail

      • getBackingDeque

        protected abstract java.util.Deque<E> getBackingDeque(int initialSize)
        Get the list that deque be used to hold the elements in this SetQueue and ensure deque properties. This deque should be empty and a reference to it should be unavailable to it outside of this method's scope. As this class generally calls this backing list for all of the methods specified in the Deque interface, the specific advantages and disadvantages of the deque returned by this method are inherited by this instance.

        This method is used in the constructor, and should not be used elsewhere. This method should return a new empty instance of the backing deque type, not a reference to the deque used in this instance. That is, if this method is called repeatedly, a new object should be return, not a reference to one which has already been created. This requirement is to ensure data encapsulation in the SetDeque implementation.

        Parameters:
        initialSize - The size to initialize the deque with. If a value less than 0 is entered, then a deque with the default size should be returned.
        Returns:
        an empty deque.
